Here are a few updates on arcmip.  From what I am hearing most of the 
groups are making excellent progress towards completing their 
simulations and getting them ready for JOSS.

The CASPR and ISCCP satellite data sets are almost finished in terms 
of interpolating to ease grid, and comparison with sheba data is 
underway.  will keep  you posted on this.

The ARCMIP BAMS article is underway, hope to have a very rough draft 
out for comments fairly soon

Colin has raised a few issues of relevance to the whole group.

For the 1D output at sheba grid pint, for the advective tendencies 
save  only the adiabatic tendencies, vertical and horizontal 
tendencies separately.

For height of lowest cloud base, hugh morrison and matt shupe have 
been using 10^-5 g m-3 as a threshold value in comparison of model 
with cloud radar for sheba,  not terribly sensitive to the threshold 
value between 10^-3 and 10^-7 g m^-3.  For those models allowing 
fraction, this is less straightforward, because there are so many 
ways this can be handled incl overlap issues, etc.  Would be open to 
anything that anyone has to suggest here

Klaus reports that the new GLIMPSE homepage is at 
<http://www.awi-potsdam.de/www-pot/atmo/glimpse/index.html>http://www.awi-potsdam.de/www-pot/atmo/glimpse/index.html

As far as I know we are still on for the next ARCMIP workshop in in 
Potsdam on 2 and 3 June 2003, in conjunction with the GLIMPSE 
meeting.  Definitely gives us a deadline for getting things done!

Judy




--============_-1168607548==_ma============
