Dear GIS Advisory Group,

I would like to announce a couple of GIS-related news.

1. The GIS Initiative web site has been updated. The new url is: 
http://www.gis.ucar.edu
2. NCAR now has a site license for ESRI GIS software. To see access and 
installation guidelines, please visit: http://www.gis.ucar.edu/license.html
3. We will be offering two free introductory ArcGIS classes for 
NCAR-UCAR staff. Two two-day classes are scheduled for March 6-7, 2003 
and March 10-11, 2003. Classes will be taught by ESRI instructors and 
will take place at UCAR Corporate Training Center at Pearl Street. Seats 
are limited (12 students per class), so first come... To sign up, 
interested individuals need to send me e-mail with the following 
information:

1. Name of the participant
2. Dates of the class (March 6-7 or March 10-11)

Cheers,
Olga

