---TITLE:
ARCSyM ar05 model output for ARCMIP


---AUTHOR(S):
John Cassano and Amanda Lynch

Contact information:
John Cassano
Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Sciences
University of Colorado
216 UCB
Boulder, CO 80309
phone: 303-492-2221
fax: 303-492-1149
e-mail: cassano@cires.colorado.edu
web: http://cires.colorado.edu/arcsym/


---FUNDING SOURCE AND GRANT NUMBER
National Science Foundation


---DATA SET OVERVIEW:

ARCMIP experiment 1 model output from ARCSyM (Arctic Regional Climate System Model).

See http://paos.colorado.edu/~curryja/arcmip/index.html for a description of
the ARCMIP experiment.

Time period: 1 Sep 1997 through 30 Sep 1998

Data location: Polar stereographic model domain centered at 72N and 153W. The domain consists
of 70 grid points in the e/w direction and 55 grid points in the n/s direction, with a grid
spacing of 50 km.
Lower left corner: 56.03N, 179.08E
Upper right corner: 72.57N, 79.18W

Data source: ARCSyM model output

Relevant web pages:
http://cires.colorado.edu/arcsym/
http://cires.colorado.edu/arcsym/arcinfo.html
http://paos.colorado.edu/~curryja/arcmip/index.html


---INSTRUMENT DESCRIPTION:
ARCSyM version 4.1
http://cires.colorado.edu/arcsym/arcinfo.html


---DATA COLLECTION and PROCESSING:


---DATA FORMAT:

Files: arcsym_ar05_metadata.txt
         ASCII file with description of model configuration for model run ar05.

       arcsym_ar05_domain.nc
         NetCDF file
         Contains model domain information (terrain elevation, latitude,
         and longitude at each model grid point).

       arcsym_ar05_mon_yymm.nc
         NetCDF files for each yymm from 9709 to 9809.
         Contain monthly mean values at the surface and on constant pressure
         levels for all model horizontal grid points (including lateral boundary
         forcing zones).

       arcsym_ar05_col_yymmdd.nc
         NetCDF files for each yymmdd from 970901 to 980930.
         Contains instantaneous 3h values at surface and on constant pressure
         levels for 9 model horizontal grid points centered on the SHEBA ship location.

       arcsym_ar05_may_yymmdd.nc
         NetCDF files for each yymmdd from 980501 to 980531.
         Contains instantaneous 3h values at surface and on constant pressure levels
         for all model horizontal grid locations (including lateral boundary
         forcing zones).


---DATA REMARKS:


---REFERENCES:





