Hi Jim

I just spoke with Math. There is some concern about having the
model data at 50km and the validation data at 25km. My opinion
is that we are better off to keep the observational data at a
relatively high resolution, and each modeling group can interpolate
or average that data to coarser resolution if needed. Also, by
having the higher resolution observational data the modelers can
assess sub-grid scale variability.

With all of that said, Math made the point that he wasn't aware of
a 50km EASE grid. I thought the EASE grid could be used at any resolution,
and with us choosing a 50km grid it would be easily compatible with
the 25km grid he is using for the observational data. Could you provide
us with the details for the 50km EASE grid you plan on using? I think
it is essential that the 50km EASE grid points align with everyother
25km EASE grid point of the observational data.

I'd appreciate your thoughts on this. Since JOSS just got the first
model output and the interpolation hasn't begun yet it seems best to
settle these issues now.

Thanks,
John

