>It was also my understanding that EASE-grid is a system, including
>both a project and a grid definition:
>
>"(EASE-Grid) consists of a set of three equal-area projections,
>combined with an infinite number of possible grid definitions."
>http://nsidc.org/data/ease/ease_grid.html
>
>Anybody can define what is appropriate for their project.
>That is why we are asking questions.
>
>The CASPR data we have is at:
>http://www.joss.ucar.edu/cgi-bin/codiac/dss?61.002
