  Hi John,

    The CASPR data you have at JOSS was
 submitted by me in early December. The
 original data from which this subset was
 produced is the SHEBA AVHRR Full Arctic 25 km
 Retrievals produced using the Cloud and Surface Parameter
 Retrieval ( CASPR ) algorithms produced by Jeff Key
 and available at  stratus.ssec.wisc.edu/products .

    The data files submitted to JOSS ( caspr_arcmip_1997.tar.gz
 and caspr_arcmip_1998.tar.gz ) are subsets of the above data
 for the years 1997-1998 covering the 'ARCMIP region' as given
 in the domain.txt file. As such they have the resolution of
 the domain.txt file ( ~ 50 km ) and are not related to the
 EASE grid.

    I am in the process of producing new CASPR data files that
 do correspond to the `new' ARCMIP region using the EASE grid.
 I have programs to produce this data set assuming a 25 km
 resolution and a region defined by columns 200 -> 520 and
 rows 200 -> 520 in the Northern Hemisphere EASE coordinates.
 It appears now that I should wait until the final resolution
 and ARCMIP region are defined.

                            Randy Reeder
                            reeder@cloud.colorado.edu


